content:
What Exactly Is a Dashboard Component?

A dashboard component is the type of widget that dashboard builders use to group and reuse common parts of multiple dashboards. They’re efficient, giving your dashboards a consistent look and feel. Create a uniform experience for users by building and managing dashboard components.

What Makes Dashboard Components Special?
They’re collaborative. Build dashboards as a team when you share and reuse dashboard components.
Look for repetition. Are there common elements in multiple dashboards? Use dashboard components to manage these common elements.

Use Dashboard Components Effectively
Make a plan before creating dashboard components. Create components that fulfill one purpose or contain unique content. Make components easy to maintain, with clear naming conventions and accessible contents.

Dashboard Components Considerations

You can add up to 10 dashboard components to a dashboard, each containing up to 20 pages.
Layouts aren’t supported in dashboard components.
Components saved in private apps are visible only by you.
Deleting a component used in other dashboards deletes its contents, but not the component itself.
To make elements interact with others in the dashboard, set "Allow filtering and faceting" for the component.
title: Understanding Dashboard Components in Salesforce
